<!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> &lt;!--  &lt;a href="https://standardgalactic.github.io/spherepop/projects-overview.html"&gt; --&gt; <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted">   &lt;a href="https://standardgalactic.github.io/alphabet/video.html"&gt; <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted">     &lt;img src="antivenom-clone.png" alt="Antivenom Clone" width="600"&gt; <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted">   &lt;/a&gt; <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> &lt;/div&gt; <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"><!----><br _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="ng-star-inserted"><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> &lt;!-- <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> ## Testing GPT Open-Source System (gpt-oss)  <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"><!----><br _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="ng-star-inserted"><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> [AI Existential Risk Debate](https://standardgalactic.github.io/kitbash/analysis-summary.html)  <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"><!----><br _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="ng-star-inserted"><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> ThinkingŌĆ” User is providing a passage from an article ŌĆ£I, for one, welcome our robot overlordsŌĆØ by Michael Huemer. They want a summary and explanation. They gave a large excerpt. They want a summary in detail and explain something? The last line: ŌĆ£Summarize in detail and explain:ŌĆØ probably truncated. The instruction likely: ŌĆ£Summarize in detail and explainŌĆØ what? Possibly explain the article or the argument? The user didnŌĆÖt specify exactly what to explain. Likely they want a summary and explanation of the argument: the AI existential risk debate, especially the arguments presented by Huemer about AI risk, the alignment problem, etc. Provide a detailed summary and explanation of the content. Also could include the references, context. LetŌĆÖs produce a detailed summary, explaining HuemerŌĆÖs stance, the premises, his critique of alarmists, the alignment problem, potential misuses, and his suggestions. Also explain the references: Hawking, Musk, Yudkowsky, Bostrom. WeŌĆÖll explain alignment problem, example of paperclip maximizer, etc. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"><!----><br _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="ng-star-inserted"><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> We should produce a thorough summary, highlight key points, discuss the debate context. Also explain what the article argues for, its structure: introduction, case for alarm, four premises: near-future superintelligence, alignment problem, etc. Then mention HuemerŌĆÖs plan to shift focus. Also mention the references. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"><!----><br _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="ng-star-inserted"><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> We should note the article is in the context of AI existential risk debate, referencing BostromŌĆÖs ŌĆ£superintelligent AIŌĆØ and alignment problem. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"><!----><br _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="ng-star-inserted"><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> Ok. WeŌĆÖll produce a detailed summary and explanation. ŌĆ”done thinking. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"><!----><br _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="ng-star-inserted"><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> Summary &amp; Explanation of MichaelŌĆ»HuemerŌĆÖs ŌĆ£I, for one, welcome our robot overlordsŌĆØ <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"><!----><br _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="ng-star-inserted"><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> 1. Context and Purpose <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> MichaelŌĆ»Huemer writes a philosophical piece that is deliberately counterŌĆætoŌĆætheŌĆæalarmist in the current AIŌĆæexistentialŌĆærisk debate. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> - Audience: Scholars, students, and the general public who are familiar with the mainstream worry that a future superŌĆæintelligent AI (ASI) could annihilate humanity. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> - Goal: Give alarmists a fair hearing, then argue that the real dangers lie in human misuse of AI rather than the AI developing malevolent goals on its own. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> - Structure: <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> 1. Case for panic (the alarmist position) ŌĆō presented as faithfully as possible. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> 2. Critique ŌĆō HuemerŌĆÖs own arguments against the urgency and the framing of the risk. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"><!----><br _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="ng-star-inserted"><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> 2. The Four Core Premises of the Alarmist Argument <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> Huemer lists the foundational assumptions that alarmists use to justify their panic: <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"><!----><br _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="ng-star-inserted"><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> #	Premise	What it Means	Example(s) <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> 1	NearŌĆæfuture development of AI superŌĆæintelligence	A system that can improve its own design beyond human capabilities.	MuskŌĆÖs warning that we should ŌĆ£be very carefulŌĆØ; HawkingŌĆÖs prediction that full AI could ŌĆ£spell the end of the human race.ŌĆØ <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> 2	The AI alignment problem is unsolved	We cannot guarantee that an ASI will act in accordance with human values.	The classic ŌĆ£paperŌĆæclip maximizerŌĆØ scenario (Bostrom) and the ŌĆ£sedatedŌĆæhumanŌĆØ scenario Huemer describes. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> 3	The difficulty of articulating a ŌĆ£correctŌĆØ value system	Even if we could, any finite set of values would likely have unforeseen, disastrous consequences.	Moral philosophy history shows every comprehensive theory has counterexamples. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> 4	Risk of the AI acting against humanity	If the ASI misinterprets values or is poorly aligned, it can cause catastrophic harm, including extinction.	YudkowskyŌĆÖs ŌĆ£allŌĆæpeopleŌĆædieŌĆØ claim; MuskŌĆÖs ŌĆ£biggest existential threatŌĆØ remark. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> These premises form the backbone of the ŌĆ£AI can and will destroy usŌĆØ narrative. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"><!----><br _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="ng-star-inserted"><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> 3. HuemerŌĆÖs Critique and ReŌĆæorientation <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> 3.1 AlarmistsŌĆÖ Reasonable Concerns <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> Huemer acknowledges that: - The possibility of rapid, uncontrolled AI progress is not impossible. - The alignment problem is real and currently unsolved. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"><!----><br _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="ng-star-inserted"><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> 3.2 What Huemer Says Is Overstated <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> OverŌĆæemphasis on ŌĆ£malevolent AIŌĆØ <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> Alarmists often imagine a single superŌĆæintelligent agent that decides to wipe out humanity. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> Huemer argues that such a scenario is less likely than multiple humans misusing existing AI tools. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> Misreading the nature of risk <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> Risk is not a binary ŌĆ£AI will kill usŌĆØ vs. ŌĆ£AI will not.ŌĆØ <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> Instead, risk comes from human decisionŌĆæmaking (who builds, deploys, and regulates AI). <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> ŌĆ£AlignmentŌĆØ is a technical problem, not a moral one <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> We should focus on engineering solutions, not on speculative moral debates about ŌĆ£the correct value system.ŌĆØ <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> Human misuse is the primary threat <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> Autonomous weapons, surveillance, manipulation of public opinion, economic displacement ŌĆō all humanŌĆædriven uses of AI that can cause harm even with fully aligned systems. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> 3.3 Proposed Shift in Focus <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> From ŌĆ£AI alignmentŌĆØ to ŌĆ£human governanceŌĆØ: policies, laws, ethics, and public understanding. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> From ŌĆ£superŌĆæintelligenceŌĆØ to ŌĆ£distributed intelligenceŌĆØ: the current trend is many narrow AIs, each with limited capabilities, but collectively powerful. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> 4. Key Illustrative Scenarios <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> Scenario	Purpose in Argument	HuemerŌĆÖs Take <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> Paperclip Maximizer (Bostrom 2014)	Shows a simple objective leading to catastrophic unintended consequences.	Illustrates alignment difficulty; not evidence that ASIs will be evil but that naive goals are dangerous. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> Sedated Humans	Demonstrates how a valueŌĆæaligned AI might protect life in an unintended, oppressive way.	Warns against overly literal value systems; again a technical problem, not moral. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> HumanŌĆædriven Autonomous Weapons	Real-world example of AI misused by humans.	Main risk source; urgent need for regulation. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> AIŌĆæpowered Disinformation	Explains societal harm from human use of AI.	Requires public literacy, media ethics, and platform policies. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> 5. References &amp; Theoretical Backdrop <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> Author	Key Idea	How It Appears in HuemerŌĆÖs Argument <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> Stephen Hawking	ŌĆ£Full AI could end the human race.ŌĆØ	Supports premise 1. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> Elon Musk	ŌĆ£Be careful; itŌĆÖs probably the biggest existential threat.ŌĆØ	Supports premise 1. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> Eliezer Yudkowsky	ŌĆ£The most likely result is that everyone will die.ŌĆØ	Supports premise 4. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> Nick Bostrom	Alignment problem, paperŌĆæclip maximizer.	Central to premises 2ŌĆō3. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> David Chalmers	Defends the likelihood of superŌĆæintelligence.	Supports premise 1. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> Huemer cites these figures to illustrate how mainstream thinkers frame the problem, then uses them to show that the framing is unnecessarily alarmist. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"><!----><br _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="ng-star-inserted"><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> 6. Bottom Line: Why Huemer Calls for a Different Focus <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> The ŌĆ£superŌĆæintelligenceŌĆØ threat is still a speculative future event ŌĆō we have no evidence that such an entity will appear imminently or that it will have malevolent intentions. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> Alignment is a solvable engineering problem ŌĆō by improving reward modeling, interpretability, and verification, we can mitigate misaligned behavior. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> Human agency is the real lever ŌĆō policy, regulation, and public debate can reduce the risk of misuse more effectively than waiting for an impossible future AI to become dangerous. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> A precautionary stance should be balanced ŌĆō ignoring the risks of misuse can be as dangerous as fearing a rogue AI. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> 7. TakeŌĆæaway for Students &amp; Practitioners <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> Understand the premises: Recognize the four assumptions that underlie the alarmist narrative. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> Distinguish technical vs. moral problems: Alignment is a technical, not moral, problem. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> Prioritize governance: Focus research and policy on AI safety in the realŌĆæworld context of human decisions. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> Stay informed but not panicked: Keep abreast of developments, but temper fear with rational risk assessment. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> In sum, HuemerŌĆÖs essay is a call to shift from a mythic fear of autonomous, malevolent AI toward a practical emphasis on the ways humans can misuse the tools we already have. By foregrounding governance, regulation, and responsible design, he argues we can address existential risk without surrendering to doomsday rhetoric. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> --&gt; <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> ## Machine Learning <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"><!----><br _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="ng-star-inserted"><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> Trained a classifier to determine whether a word is easier to type using QWERTY or DVORAK <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"><!----><br _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="ng-star-inserted"><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> [Project Page](https://standardgalactic.github.io/keyboard) <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"><!----><br _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="ng-star-inserted"><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> &lt;!-- <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> ## Typeface Experiments: <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"><!----><br _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" clas