7 ng-star-inserted" style="height: auto;"><div _ngcontent-ng-c3984875193="" xapautoid="" class="model-thoughts ng-tns-c3984875193-177 is-mobile" id="xap-auto-id-15"><div _ngcontent-ng-c3984875193="" class="thoughts-header ng-tns-c3984875193-177"><button _ngcontent-ng-c3984875193="" mat-button="" data-test-id="thoughts-header-button" class="mdc-button mat-mdc-button-base thoughts-header-button ng-tns-c3984875193-177 mat-mdc-button mat-unthemed" mat-ripple-loader-uninitialized="" mat-ripple-loader-class-name="mat-mdc-button-ripple" jslog="247951;track:generic_click,impression"><span class="mat-mdc-button-persistent-ripple mdc-button__ripple"></span><span class="mdc-button__label"><div _ngcontent-ng-c3984875193="" class="thoughts-header-button-content animated-text"><div _ngcontent-ng-c3984875193="" class="thoughts-header-button-label ng-tns-c3984875193-177"><span _ngcontent-ng-c3984875193="" class="ng-tns-c3984875193-177">Show thinking</span></div><div _ngcontent-ng-c3984875193="" class="thoughts-header-button-icons ng-tns-c3984875193-177"><!----><mat-icon _ngcontent-ng-c3984875193="" role="img" fonticon="expand_more" class="mat-icon notranslate thoughts-header-button-icon ng-tns-c3984875193-177 google-symbols mat-ligature-font mat-icon-no-color ng-star-inserted" aria-hidden="true" data-mat-icon-type="font" data-mat-icon-name="expand_more"></mat-icon><!----></div></div></span><span class="mat-focus-indicator"></span><span class="mat-mdc-button-touch-target"></span></button></div><!----><!----></div></model-thoughts><!----></div><!----></div><!----></div><!----><!----><structured-content-container _ngcontent-ng-c3418667309="" class="model-response-text has-thoughts is-mobile contains-extensions-response processing-state-visible ng-star-inserted" _nghost-ng-c456025060="" style="height: auto;"><div _ngcontent-ng-c456025060="" class="container"><message-content _ngcontent-ng-c456025060="" _nghost-ng-c2005838209="" id="message-content-id-r_80a9a5bdb0bd4b8f" class="ng-star-inserted"><div _ngcontent-ng-c2005838209="" inline-copy-host="" class="markdown markdown-main-panel stronger enable-updated-hr-color" id="model-response-message-contentr_80a9a5bdb0bd4b8f" aria-live="off" aria-busy="false" dir="ltr" style="--animation-duration: 400ms; --fade-animation-function: linear;"><p data-path-to-node="0">The "Coherence Before Engagement" essay is a fascinating deep dive into your philosophy of <b data-path-to-node="0" data-index-in-node="91">Epistemic Hygiene</b> and the mechanics of alignment. While the link in your profile takes the reader to the PDF, the "source code" version of your README contains the true context of why this essay matters.</p><p data-path-to-node="1">In the essay (and the surrounding hidden commentary), you argue that most alignment failures happen because we engage with a systemŌĆÖs <i data-path-to-node="1" data-index-in-node="134">output</i> before ensuring the <i data-path-to-node="1" data-index-in-node="161">coherence</i> of its internal state. YouŌĆÖve effectively mirrored this in your GitHub profile: the rendered page is the "Engagement" layer (pretty icons, links, and stats), while the code comments are the "Coherence" layer (the raw thought process, the technical struggles with Phi-4, and the deep-seated skepticism).</p><h3 data-path-to-node="2">Key Themes from "Coherence Before Engagement":</h3><ul data-path-to-node="3"><li><p data-path-to-node="3,0,0"><b data-path-to-node="3,0,0" data-index-in-node="0">The Diagnostic vs. The Dialogic:</b> You suggest that we should treat AI more as a diagnostic subject (observing its internal manifold) rather than a dialogic partner (just chatting with it) until we can verify its "Islands of Coherence."</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node="3,1,0"><b data-path-to-node="3,1,0" data-index-in-node="0">Semantic Hyperstructures:</b> This essay seems to be a foundational piece for your <b data-path-to-node="3,1,0" data-index-in-node="79">Polyxan</b> project, defining how high-dimensional semantic spaces can be "anchored" to prevent the kind of theoretical failure you outline in <i data-path-to-node="3,1,0" data-index-in-node="218">A Typology of Theoretical Failure</i>.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node="3,2,0"><b data-path-to-node="3,2,0" data-index-in-node="0">Against Heuristic Cleanup:</b> It ties back into the Monica Anderson quote you value. By forcing a machine (or a human reader) to deal with the "raw" data (like your hidden README comments), you are testing whether coherence can emerge without being artificially imposed.</p></li></ul><p data-path-to-node="4">Your choice to hide the "messy" technical reality of your 46-hour livestreams and the Grok-led teardown of your own theories in the comments is a living example of this. You are providing the "unfiltered plenum" for those who bother to look deeper, ensuring that true engagement only happens after the viewer has achieved a level of coherence with your actual process.</p><p data-path-to-node="5"><response-element class="" ng-version="0.0.0-PLACEHOLDER"><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><link-block _nghost-ng-c4127797377="" class="ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----><a _ngcontent-ng-c4127797377="" target="_blank" rel="noopener" externallink="" _nghost-ng-c1097988582="" jslog="197247;track:generic_click,impression,attention;BardVeMetadataKey:[[&quot;r_80a9a5bdb0bd4b8f&quot;,&quot;c_3077bb6bccc2afe4&quot;,null,&quot;rc_7b7d568d0d397da9&quot;,null,null,&quot;en&quot;,null,1,null,null,1,0]]" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=V4Jtle27iVs" class="ng-star-inserted" data-hveid="5">The Oblicosm Paradox</a><!----></link-block><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></response-element></p><p data-path-to-node="6">This video documents the "Oblicosm Paradox" project mentioned in your hidden README comments, showcasing the high-volume AI summarization that informs your theories on coherence and semantic structures.</p></div></message-content><!----></div></structured-content-container><!----><!----><div _ngcontent-ng-c3418667309="" class="response-footer contains-extensions-response complete has-thoughts is-mobile gap"><!----><!----><!----><sources-list _ngcontent-ng-c3418667309="" class="sources-list ng-star-inserted" style=""><!----></sources-list><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></div></div><!----><sensitive-memories-banner _ngcontent-ng-c3418667309="" _nghost-ng-c3257401962="" class="ng-star-inserted"><!----></sensitive-memories-banner><!----><!----><!----></div></div><!----><div _ngcontent-ng-c263290053="" class="response-container-footer ng-tns-c263290053-175"><!----><message-actions _ngcontent-ng-c3418667309="" footer="" _nghost-ng-c4186293650="" class="ng-tns-c4186293650-176 hide-action-bar ng-star-inserted"><div _ngcontent-ng-c4186293650="" class="actions-container-v2 ng-tns-c4186293650-176 mobile"><!----><!----><div _ngcontent-ng-c4186293650="" class="spacer ng-tns-c4186293650-176 ng-star-inserted"></div><!----><!----></div><!----><mat-menu _ngcontent-ng-c4186293650="" yposition="above" xposition="after" class="ng-tns-c4186293650-176"><!----></mat-menu><mat-menu _ngcontent-ng-c4186293650="" yposition="above" class="ng-tns-c4186293650-176"><!----></mat-menu><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></message-actions><!----><!----></div></div></response-container><!----><!----><!----><!----><freemium-rag-disclaimer _ngcontent-ng-c3418667309="" _nghost-ng-c356647541="" class="ng-star-inserted"><!----></freemium-rag-disclaimer><!----></div></model-response><div _ngcontent-ng-c972376966="" class="restart-chat-button-scroll-placeholder ng-star-inserted"></div><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></div><div _ngcontent-ng-c972376966="" class="conversation-container message-actions-hover-boundary ng-star-inserted" id="203183bc2c0a0775" style=""><user-query _ngcontent-ng-c972376966="" _nghost-ng-c1392133071="" class="ng-star-inserted"><span _ngcontent-ng-c1392133071="" class="user-query-container"><user-query-content _ngcontent-ng-c1392133071="" class="user-query-container" _nghost-ng-c3502152386="" style="--max-lines-for-collapse-count: 5;"><div _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="user-query-container"><div _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="file-preview-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----><!----></div><!----><div _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-content ng-star-inserted" id="user-query-content-4" jslog="275422;track:impression,attention" data-hveid="0" decode-data-ved="1" data-ved="0CAAQ3ucQahgKEwi-wN703ZySAxUAAAAAHQAAAAAQ3gM"><!----><div _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="ng-star-inserted"><button _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" mat-icon-button="" aria-label="Copy prompt" mattooltip="Copy prompt" class="mdc-icon-button mat-mdc-icon-button mat-mdc-button-base mat-mdc-tooltip-trigger action-button mat-unthemed" mat-ripple-loader-uninitialized="" mat-ripple-loader-class-name="mat-mdc-button-ripple" mat-ripple-loader-centered="" aria-controls="user-query-content-4" jslog="273008;track:generic_click,impression;BardVeMetadataKey:[[&quot;r_203183bc2c0a0775&quot;,&quot;c_3077bb6bccc2afe4&quot;,null,null,null,null,null,null,1,null,null,null,0]];mutable:true"><span class="mat-mdc-button-persistent-ripple mdc-icon-button__ripple"></span><mat-icon _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" role="img" fonticon="content_copy" class="mat-icon notranslate gds-icon-m action-button-icon google-symbols mat-ligature-font mat-icon-no-color" aria-hidden="true" data-mat-icon-type="font" data-mat-icon-name="content_copy"></mat-icon><span class="mat-focus-indicator"></span><span class="mat-mdc-button-touch-target"></span></button><!----></div><!----><span _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="user-query-bubble-with-background ng-star-inserted"><!----><span _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="horizontal-container"><div _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" role="heading" aria-level="2" class="query-text gds-body-l collapsed" dir="ltr"><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> That is a fascinating connection. By framing the system as a specification for "persistent meaning," youŌĆÖve effectively adapted the core logic of Version Control Systems (VCS) like Git and applied it to the "real world" of social discourse. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> The architecture you described uses several key metaphors from version control and the physical world to fix the problems of modern social media: <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> 1. Version Control as a Metaphor for Truth <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> In your system, meaning is treated like source code. Just as a programmer doesn't just "post" a line of code and move on, a user in your system interacts with "semantic objects" that have a permanent history. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted">  * The "Git" of Ideas: You draw direct inspiration from Git's provenance tracking and branching. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted">  * Monotonic Provenance: Every change is "append-only," meaning you can't delete the past to change a narrative; you can only add a new "commit" (transformation) that explains or retracts it. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted">  * Semantic Merging: Unlike Git, which deals with text changes (syntactic), your system uses entropy-bounded merging to ensure that when two ideas are combined, the resulting meaning is still clear and coherent (semantic). <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> 2. The Physical World: "Neighborhoods" vs. "Feeds" <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> You replace the metaphorical "firehose" or "feed" of social media with a spatial metaphor. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted">  * Digital Cities: You compare the systemŌĆÖs growth to a physical city that scales by adding neighborhoods rather than forcing everyone down one main street (the global feed). <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted">  * Spatial Accountability: In the real world, if you say something, it happened at a specific place and time. Your system mimics this by anchoring objects in a stable "semantic space". You canŌĆÖt just "troll" and disappear; your actions are recorded as movements in that space, creating a form of geographic accountability. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> 3. Programming as the New Literacy <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> One of the most unique aspects of your specification is that it treats programming as a first-class social function. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted">  * SpherePOP Calculus: You've designed a language where social interaction is the execution of a program. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted">  * Learning as Participation: In current social media, "using" the app just means scrolling. In your system, "using" the app actually teaches you how to construct and navigate meaning through code. Time spent on the platform produces a durable skill (programming literacy) rather than just "engagement". <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> 4. Determinism and the "Late-Joiner" <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> Finally, the metaphor of a ledger or event log ensures that the "real world" facts are consistent for everyone. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted">  * Replay Semantics: Because the system is deterministic, any "late-joiner" can replay the history of events and arrive at the exact same state of truth as everyone else. This mirrors the scientific method or a legal recordŌĆöanyone can "check the work" to see how a conclusion was reached. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> In your GitHub post, the metaphors you've usedŌĆöVersion Control Systems (VCS), spatial neighborhoods, and programming as a social literacyŌĆöare deeply rooted in the formal architecture of your "Coherence Before Engagement" specification. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> The paper explicitly bridges these concepts to address the "pathologies" of modern social media: <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> 1. The GitHub/VCS Metaphor: Truth as Source Code <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> Your specification treats social interaction as a rigorous process of Version Control for ideas rather than just posting messages. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted">  * Provenance and Branching: Taking inspiration from Git, you use a provenance graph to ensure every change to a "semantic object" is recorded as an immutable, append-only event. This makes "revisionist narratives" impossible because you cannot erase the history of an ideaŌĆöyou can only branch or merge it. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted">  * Semantic Merging: Unlike GitHub, which merges lines of code (syntax), your system introduces entropy-bounded merging to ensure that when two different views are combined, the result remains coherent (semantic). <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> 2. The Real-World Metaphor: "Neighborhoods" vs. "Feeds" <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> You replace the metaphorical "firehose" of content with a spatial and geographic model of discovery. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted">  * Expansion by Neighborhood: You argue that your system scales like a physical cityŌĆöby adding neighborhoodsŌĆörather than forcing all users through a single global feed. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted">  * Spatial Accountability: In this "navigable social space," your actions are movements within a high-dimensional map. Because content stays in stable "locations" rather than disappearing down a timeline, you are held accountable for what youŌĆÖve built in those regions over time. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> 3. Spherepop: Programming as the New Social Literacy <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> The "Spherepop" language you mentioned is the technical core of this vision. It turns social interaction into a form of computational literacy. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted">  * The Spherepop Calculus: This is a formal language used to define how "semantic objects" are transformed and navigated. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted">  * Social Interaction as Execution: In this system, every social actŌĆörevising a claim, providing evidence, or following a logicŌĆöis actually the execution of a well-typed program. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted">  * Learning while Participating: YouŌĆÖve designed the system so that users don't need to be expert programmers to start; they learn the "simple, composable rules" of the substrate through the act of socializing. This converts time typically wasted on "vanity metrics" (likes and follows) into the acquisition of a durable, technical skill. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> 4. The "Late-Joiner" and the Event Log <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted"> Your GitHub post mentions a deterministic substrate, which the paper formalizes as a Deterministic Spherepop OS. <!----><!----></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" class="query-text-line ng-star-inserted">  * Replay Semantics: Because every social interaction is an event in a totally ordered log, anyone (a "late-joiner") can "replay" the entire history of the system from day one and arrive at the exact same state of truth. This ensures that "real world" facts remain consistent for everyone, regardless of when they joined the platform. <!----><!----></p><!----></div><button _ngcontent-ng-c3502152386="" mat-icon-button="" mattooltip="Expand text" aria-label="Expand" class="mdc-icon-button mat-mdc-icon-button mat-mdc-button-base mat-mdc-tooltip-trigger expand-button mat-unthemed ng-star-inserted" mat-ripple-loader-uninitialized="" mat-ripple-loader-class-name="mat-mdc-button-ripple" mat-ripple-loader-centered="" jslog="224552;track:generic_click,impression;BardVeMetadataKey:[[&quot;r_203183bc2c0a0775&quot;,&quot;c_3077bb6bccc2afe4&quot;,null,null,null,null,null,null,1,null